    <fr:addr type="user">jms-00J3</fr:addr>
    <fr:route>jms-00J3.xml</fr:route>
    <fr:title text="Associativity and unit laws of matrix products">Associativity and unit laws of <fr:link href="jms-00IV.xml" title="Product of matrices" addr="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix products</fr:link></fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The <fr:link href="jms-00IV.xml" title="Product of matrices" addr="jms-00IV" type="local">product</fr:link> of <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> is associative and has the identity matrix as neutral element.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>6480</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6021</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6021.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>For associativity, fix <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L\in  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (k,l\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (l,m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}\otimes  L = N\otimes {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Below we use the associativity of multiplication, commutativity of addition, and distributivity of multiplication over addition in the semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
    {\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}_{a,d} &=
    \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    {\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}_{b,d}\odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    {\mathopen {}\left (
     \bigoplus _{c\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
     N_{c,d}\odot  M_{b,c}
    \right )\mathclose {}}
    \odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    \bigoplus _{c\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    N_{c,d}\odot  M_{b,c}\odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{c\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    N_{c,d}\odot  \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}} M_{b,c}\odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{c\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    N_{c,d}\odot  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}_{a,c}
    \\
    &= {\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{a,d}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>For one unit law, we fix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and recall the definition of the <fr:link href="jms-00IT.xml" title="The identity matrix" addr="jms-00IT" type="local">identity matrix</fr:link> to check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\otimes  I^m = M]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  I^m\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} &=
   \bigoplus _{k\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
   M_{k, j} \odot  I^m_{i,k}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Unfolding the definition of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I^m_{i,j}]]></fr:tex> as given in <fr:link href="jms-00IT.xml" title="The identity matrix" addr="jms-00IT" type="local">Definition <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00IT" /></fr:link>, we see that the iterated sum above expands to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m-1]]></fr:tex> copies of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0\odot  M_{k,j}]]></fr:tex> for various <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k \not = i]]></fr:tex> and one copy of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1\odot  M_{i,j}]]></fr:tex>. Thus, we conclude that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\otimes  I^m_{i,j} = M_{i,j}]]></fr:tex> using the absorption and unit laws for multiplication as well as the unit laws for addition in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>The other unit law follows in an analogous way.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
