                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IU</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00IU.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Matrix multiplication in geometry">Matrix multiplication in geometry</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Although we do not explore it in <fr:link href="jms-00XY.xml" title="IA Discrete Mathematics" addr="jms-00XY" type="local">this course</fr:link>, the viewpoint of matrix multiplication as relational composition generalises to a correct explanation of the role of matrices in geometry as presentations of linear maps between vector spaces in terms of an (uncanonical) choice of basis.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>6479</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IV</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00IV.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Product of matrices">Product of <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (l\times  m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> be a <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span>. The <fr:em><fr:strong>product</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\otimes  N]]></fr:tex>, is the following <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (l\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span>:</fr:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 {\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}_{i\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}},j\in {\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}} =
 \bigoplus _{k\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}} N_{k,j}\odot  M_{i,k}
]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                  <fr:contributor>
                    <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
                  </fr:contributor>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
